<subSubSection pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="153.[136,778,1155,1947]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,258,1155,1181]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[404,560,1156,1182]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonia">
<emphasis box="[404,560,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. patagonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="153" pageNumber="154" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 29 A–H) resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[628,778,1192,1218]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osbournei">
<emphasis box="[628,778,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. osbournei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[144,279,1228,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 133" captionStartId="147.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-126@147.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="147" captionText="FIGURE 133. Actinopus osbournei sp. nov., male: A–F MCTP 8859 (Automontage photos) and MCTP 8850 (SEM Images): A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597518/files/figure.png" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Fig. 133 C</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[307,388,1228,1254]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dioi">
<emphasis box="[307,388,1228,1254]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. dioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[410,544,1228,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 136" captionStartId="150.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,206,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-197@150.[151,1435,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="150" captionText="FIGURE 136. Actinopus dioi sp. nov., male: A–F MPEG (Automontage photos) and MPEG (SEM Images): A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597528/files/figure.png" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Fig. 136 C</figureCitation>
) and all species of group 
<taxonomicName box="[211,312,1264,1290]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[211,312,1264,1290]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios, D. T." box="[330,458,1265,1291]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" pagination="73 - 77" refId="ref140396" refString="Rios, D. T. (2014) A new species of the genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) from Argentina. Acta Arachnologica, 63 (2): 73 - 77. https: // doi. org / 10.2476 / asjaa. 63.73" type="journal article" year="2014">Ríos, 2014</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1–12; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="153" pageNumber="154" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig 38 A–G, 39 A–H, 40 A–D) by two basal and two proximal sigilla merged on the middle of portions basal and proximal of sternum. They differ from those of group 
<taxonomicName box="[305,406,1410,1436]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[305,406,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of central depression on the middle of sternum. They resemble those of the two species of group 
<taxonomicName box="[329,430,1483,1509]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[329,430,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[446,541,1483,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 135" captionStartId="149.[136,235,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,212,1160]" captionTargetId="figure-346@149.[151,1436,189,1164]" captionTargetPageId="149" captionText="FIGURE 135. Actinopus osbournei sp. nov., male: A–C MCTP 8859: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597526/files/figure.png" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Fig. 135</figureCitation>
A–C, 
<figureCitation box="[615,709,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 138" captionStartId="152.[136,235,1262,1286]" captionTargetBox="[164,1403,198,1196]" captionTargetId="figure-348@152.[151,1436,189,1238]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="FIGURE 138. Actinopus dioi sp. nov., male:A–C MPEG:A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral.PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal TegularApophysis; PAc-ProlateralAccessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597532/files/figure.png" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Fig. 138</figureCitation>
A–C) by the position of BTA on the tegulum and three keels in prolateral view of the tegulum. Differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[635,778,1556,1582]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osbournei">
<emphasis box="[635,778,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. osbournei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[185,262,1592,1619]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dioi">
<emphasis box="[185,262,1592,1619]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. dioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by wider embolus and PA developed; differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[200,277,1629,1655]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dioi">
<emphasis box="[200,277,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. dioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by elongated shape of the copulatory bulb. The females differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[450,693,1665,1692]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerschiapelliarum">
<emphasis box="[450,693,1665,1692]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">A. gerschiapelliarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018, fig. 19 C–D) by a smaller constriction below external lobes on each receptacle and by presence of pores on all the length of receptacles.
</paragraph>
